OracleTimeSpan Struct

Definition

Represents a time interval and corresponds to the Oracle 9i INTERVAL DAY TO SECOND data type.

In this Article

public struct OracleTimeSpan : IComparable, System.Data.SqlTypes.INullable
Inheritance
Object
System.ValueType
OracleTimeSpan

Remarks

The Oracle INTERVAL DAY TO SECOND data type (Oracle 9i or later) contains an interval of time in days, hours, minutes, and seconds, and has a fixed size of 11 bytes.

To obtain an OracleTimeSpan object, call the GetOracleTimeSpan method.

Fields

MaxValue

Represents the maximum valid date value for an OracleTimeSpan structure.

public static readonly System.Data.OracleClient.OracleTimeSpan MaxValue;

Remarks

The value is 10675199.02:48:05.4775807. To obtain a value greater than MaxValue, use the Oracle SELECT TO_CHAR statement. For more information about the ranges supported by the Oracle 9i INTERVAL DAY TO SECOND data type, see your Oracle documentation.

MinValue

Represents the minimum valid date value for an OracleTimeSpan structure.

public static readonly System.Data.OracleClient.OracleTimeSpan MinValue;

Remarks

The value is -10675199.02:48:05.4775808. To obtain a value less than MinValue, use the Oracle SELECT TO_CHAR statement. For more information about the ranges supported by the Oracle 9i INTERVAL DAY TO SECOND data type, see your Oracle documentation.

Null

Represents a null value that can be assigned to the stem.Data.OracleClient.OracleTimeSpan.Value* property of an instance of the OracleTimeSpan structure.

public static readonly System.Data.OracleClient.OracleTimeSpan Null;

Remarks

Null functions as a constant for the OracleTimeSpan structure.
